Second, he excludes this doubt: for thus says the Lord,

first, setting out the benefit of liberation: even the captivity, namely of the Jews: I broke the jaws of the wicked man (Job 29:17);

second, the manner of liberation, setting out the destruction of their enemies: but I will judge those, namely, the Chaldeans, that have judged you, unjustly: I will cut off all that have afflicted you (Zeph 3:19).
